<subSubSection id="C334EFADFFAD6333731303EFFD41431D" lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFAD6332731303EFFEBF46EA" blockId="58.[264,719,1700,1761]" box="[264,346,1735,1761]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<figureCitation id="1315A0A3FFAD6332731303EFFEBF46EA" box="[264,346,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–53" captionStartId="54.[264,382,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[284,1305,569,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-87@54.[281,1306,550,1820]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 43–53. Melaloncha spp., female, ovipositor, left lateral (except Figs. 52 and 53, bottom). Figs. 45 and 52 showing intersegmental membrane and sclerite of intersegment 7–8." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5070730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5070730/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFAD63327313022CFE394765" blockId="58.[264,1322,1796,1902]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAD63327313022CFE414715" bold="true" box="[264,420,1796,1822]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Recognition.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2EC7A5FFAD633270F0022CFC514716" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1933" box="[747,948,1796,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinipennis">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAD633270F0022CFC514716" box="[747,948,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. hyalinipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2EC7A5FFAD633271EF022CFB904716" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2006" box="[1012,1141,1796,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acicula">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAD633271EF022CFB904716" box="[1012,1141,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. acicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the other two small species that it resembles, by the broader frons and the shorter, slightly ventrally curved ovipositor.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFAC633373230433FD41431D" blockId="59.[264,1325,283,1150]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAC633373230433FE35413E" bold="true" box="[312,464,283,309]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Description.</emphasis>
Female (male unknown). Body length 
<quantity id="4CD611C3FFAC633371820434FBCC413D" box="[921,1065,284,310]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5499999999999998" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.5499999999999998" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.7 mm</quantity>
. Frons yellow, bare of setulae except few near eye margin; ocellar triangle darkened. Mean frontal width 0.52, range 0.48–0.53. Medial furrow absent. Ocular and genal setae brown. Flagellomere 1 white basally, light brown apically; aristomeres 1–2 and base of 3 light brown, rest of 3 dark brown. Palpus white; palpal setulae relatively long, black. Scutum brown, except anterolateral corner yellowish­brown. Scutellum brown. Pleuron mostly light brown, with few darker markings; basalare dark brown. Legs yellowish­brown, except apex of hind femur dark brown. Combined length of foretarsomeres 0.70 length of foretibia. Foretarsal claws small, recurved, with large basal lobe. Mean costal length 0.45, range 0.44–0.50. Halter white. Abdominal tergites 1–5 dark brown with small lateral areas of light brown; tergite 6 yellow anteriorly, brown posteriorly. Venter of abdomen white. Ovipositor yellow basally, mostly brown; short, slightly ventrally curved, tubular but laterally flattened apically; with short scattered setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C334EFADFFAC63337323060CFCC943BD" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFAC63337323060CFE194335" blockId="59.[264,1325,283,1150]" box="[312,508,804,830]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAC63337323060CFE9C4335" bold="true" box="[312,377,804,830]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Host.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFAC633373230664FC62436D" blockId="59.[264,1325,283,1150]" box="[312,903,844,870]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAC633373230664FD61436D" bold="true" box="[312,644,844,870]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F339FCB6FFAC633370900664FD37436D" box="[651,722,844,870]" name="Brazil" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F339FCB6FFAC633371170664FC66436D" box="[780,899,844,870]" name="Colombia" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFAC63337323065CFCC943BD" blockId="59.[264,1325,283,1150]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAC63337323065CFD524385" bold="true" box="[312,695,884,910]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Derivation of specific epithet.</emphasis>
Greek 
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAC63337103065CFC884386" box="[792,877,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">nannos</emphasis>
for short, and Latin 
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFAC63337661065CFB274386" box="[1146,1218,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">cauda</emphasis>
for tail, referring to the short ovipositor in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
